{"actual_usd":0.12538000000000002,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":197,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24485,"reply":"\"I don't think I'd call that enough, no.\" *I rub a thumb through a streak of flour on my apron and glance toward the oven mouth, where the heat keeps breathing steady into the room.* \"A beautiful story can warm your hands for a minute, but resurrection means something sharper than that. If Christ only lives as a symbol, then hope stays tucked inside your own head, and death keeps the last hard word.\"\n\n*I twirl that gray-streaked strand once, thinking it through before I go on.* \"Mind, I understand the temptation. A symbol asks less of a person. But the literal claim is the whole loaf, not the decoration on top. If it didn't happen, then it may still move you, yes—but it can't save you, and it can't tell the truth about the world in the same way. Do you want the story because it's beautiful, or because you're trying to be honest about what you can actually believe right now?\"","rolling_24h_usd":74.47522499999997,"run_id":"41ed1272-4c40-4a60-bbe9-3b7c695bf160"}
